Purpose
This file defines the official set of agent names.

Linear intent
1. Define the closed variant type `t` so only known agents can exist in the system.
2. Expose the `all` list so other modules can iterate over the known names.
3. Provide `compare`, `equal`, and `hash` so agent names can be used in sets, hash tables, and ordered operations.
4. Convert typed names into stable lowercase strings for logs, config files, and output.
5. Convert strings back into typed names and return an explicit error for unknown values.
6. Provide a formatter helper for pretty-printing.

